The directional derivative of a vector field \(V^a\) along a vector field \(W^a\) is given by the covariant derivative contracted with \(W^a\). In index notation, this is expressed as \(W^a \nabla_a V^b\), which generalizes the expression \(U^a \nabla_a U^b\) for the 4-velocity.

\boxed{W^a \nabla_a V^b}

